    "text": "Fan-out: one hole becomes all of them\n\nArrayPolar repeats ONE cylinder around a bolt circle, and the whole array is subtracted from the plate in a single Subtract \u2014 the boolean takes the list as one operand, so you never copy-paste a hole.\n\nChange the array count and the flange re-drills itself. This is the Grasshopper idea the engine is built around: wire a list, get a list."
